, † 

Gerontoformica

NEL & PERRAULT, 2004, and 

Prionopelta

MAYR, 1866) and three or four inconspicuous teeth; ventral face with a single peg-like seta (“Mps” in 
Fig. 2A, C, E
; the seta morphology is similar to that of labrum) which is located near the base of the second and third inconspicuous teeth of the masticatory margin, and two long apically spatulate setae (arrows in 
Fig. 2C, E
); trulleum apparently absent; canthellus (“Ctl” in 
Fig.2C, E
